text:
Hello hello, I have a question regarding submitting a HubSpot form to an external cold fusion database/crm. We are currently using a multi-step progressive form that is using a bit of javascript to push any HubSpot forms to the CRM and that work’s nicely. We have a challenge where we would need to send that same data to this external database. We were provided with some json that looks like the below. Would we need some kind of javascript in order to push that data through? How would we best utilize this JSON file in our multi-step form?
```{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "ID",
		"name": "find-my-agent",
		"schema": "<https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json>"
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "leads",
			"request": {
				"method": "GET",
				"header": [],
				"url": {
					"raw": ""
				}
			},
			"response": []
		}
	]
}```
